race.description: Sam Miranda Wines Dunstan Sprint Handicap (Bm70)
race.comment: Looks a good first-up option for IMPENDING WAR (13) who won his first two, including the strong Elvstroem Classic, and was then far from disgraced in what has turned out to be a strong metro 2YO race. Has been gelded since then and he's shown enough in recent jumpouts to suggest he can return a winner. SISTER SHAY (12) gets a change of rider and has been freshened up since finishing eighth over 1600m at Moonee Valley last start. Best form is good enough so worth another chance. KAGEMUSHA (16) was an impressive winner last time over 1135m at Geelong, scoring by 2.25 lengths and making it two straight wins. Can measure up here. TAP 'N' RUN (4) hasn't been far away lately, beaten 1.4 lengths at his most recent appearance when fifth over 1175m at Albury. Has a wide gate but he can figure in the finish. MATERIAL DREAMS (6) should be nearing peak fitness after three runs back from a spell and draws to get every chance.
